KW  - Inflation
KW  - Investment
KW  - Great ratios
KW  - Tobin effect
KW  - Fisher effect
AB  - Using over 100 years of U.S. data, we find that the long-run effects of inflation on consumption, investment, and output are positive. Also, great ratios like the consumption and investment rates are not independent of inflation, which we interpret in terms of the Fisher effect. However, the variability of the stochastic inflation trend is small relative to the variability of the productivity and fiscal trends. Thus, models generating long-term negative effects of inflation on output and consumption seem to be at odds with data from the moderate inflation rate environment we consider.
ER  - 

